node.text: From reefs to ridges, explore the beauty of the Philippines through the eyes of the locals. While 2020 has been a year of change for travel, the Philippines is excited to invite local visitors to explore the beautiful islands. The #BDTeam had the pleasure of working with @tourism_phl to highlight beautiful places around the Philippines. The opportunities for exploration are endless-from the Hundred Island National Park in Pangasinan to exploring the Suba and Culili Sand Dunes in Ilocos Norte.

node.text:
With an incredibly rich history, being an “Egyptian” can have many facets especially when it comes to creativity. Today, we’re sharing a unique story dedicated to any creative who intends to carve their own path no matter the circumstances. 

“It’s proof that the end product most of the time doesn’t pan out the way you expect it. And its by having expectations that you hinder your potential.” - @matiasderada

Watch this beautiful film on Beautiful Destinations Youtube channel. 🇪🇬

🎥 @matiasderada #BDTeam

Bristol Bay, one of Alaska’s most treasured natural wonders, is under threat. @world_wildlife 

It’s home to an irreplaceable ecosystem and one of the last salmon strongholds. Not only that, its iconic wildlife has sprung up a sustainable tourism industry which effects thousands of Alaskan livelihoods.

All of this is under threat if the Pebble Mine moves forward. The recent approval of the environmental impact statement has made it clear that our voices need to be heard. 

Nature and people can’t live without fresh water, and Bristol Bay is the lifeblood that sustains every species calling the region home. 

On a recent trip to Alaska, the #BDTeam and WWF Ambassador, @jeremyjauncey, learned firsthand about the conservation community’s fight against Pebble Mine.

node.text: As New York City starts to open back up, we wanted to take a moment to reflect on the efforts of heroes in the hospitality industry who have been helping our frontline workers. @fsnewyork was the first hotel in New York City to open its door to our frontline workers and provide them with a safe haven to stay during such an uncertain time. They quickly transformed the hotel into a near medical-grade facility. Over 300 medical workers called @fsnewyork home during this time as they were provided rooms free of charge. This allowed them to keep their own families safe as they focused on their work and taking care of patients. ❤️ (🎥: @loganlambert 📸: @loganstrongarms 📍: Four Seasons Hotel New York)

Walks around Milldale with @elisetanriverdi. 😌 Milldale is a quaint destination in England known for its laidback ambiance and untamed natural beauty. Here you can enjoy fishing, going on picture-perfect strolls, and sightseeing, especially if you're a fan of destinations with an old-world charm. 🌿

If you're looking for a lowkey yet charming getaway, make your way to this stone village lying in its scenic countryside! 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿

Do you prefer exploring England's bustling cities or its tranquil countryside?

📽 @elisetanriverdi
📍 Milldale, England
🎶 Austin Farwell - New Home

We're in awe of @sebpic_'s view of the Peitlerkofel mountain. 😍 Leave it to Italy's Dolomites region to always take our breaths away with its beauty and majesty. 🔥

Located in the Dolomites, the Peitlerkofel is a solitary mountain that stands between Val Badia to the east and the Villnöß valley to the west. One of the best ways to explore the area is by taking the "Peitlerkofel circular walk", a beautiful hike in the Puez-Odle Natural Park that spans about five hours around the entire base of this formidable mountain. ⛰

During your travels, would you rather explore mountains or beaches?

📽 @sebpic_
📍 Peitlerkofel, South Tyrol, Italy
🎶 Bruno Mars - Talking to the Moon

The water is lava. 😆 Doesn't @timalongi make paragliding look so easy? This was shot in the Dune of Pilat in France, known as the highest sand dune in Europe. 🇫🇷

The Dune of Pilat is one of the most visited natural sites in France due to its fascinating appearance and surroundings. The dune stretches about 2.7 km long and is approximately 500m wide and up to 110m tall. You can visit it any time of the year and is particularly popular with paragliders for its vast landscape. 🪂

Did you know this place existed in France and would you like to explore it? ✨

📽 @timalongi
📍 Dune of Pilat, France

node.text:
This romantic corner via @sennarelax is the kind of magical scenery that makes us want to explore more of the world. 😍

Tucked in southern Bosnia and Herzegovina and straddling the Neretva River, the city of Mostar is rich in culture and history. It's home to beautiful buildings, shops, and market stalls, making it a prime location for a day trip from Croatia or even a longer stay. 💐

Have you heard about this city in Bosnia & Herzegovina? Does this make you curious to explore and learn more about the place? 🇧🇦

📽 @sennarelax
📍 Mostar, Bosnia & Herzegovina
🎶 Louis Armstrong – What a Wonderful World

Would you sleep here? @aindxbofficial 

@TomJauncey from the #BDTeam had the chance to sleep up in the World’s largest and tallest observation wheel for the launch announcement of #AinDubai. 

Ain Dubai, brought to you by @dubaiholding has 48 cabins and is double the size of the London Eye.

Tickets are now on sale for the grand opening on October 21st 🎡🇦🇪.

🎥: @tomjauncey 
🎶: “Cornfield Chase” by Hans Zimmer

How amazing is this spectacle? Would you want to swim among a harmless swarm of jellyfish? 😮

Competition is tough out here! 😆 @murmeltierfotos.de shows us who she's up against while taking photographs in the Austrian Alps. 🇦🇹

Curious by nature, they're known to be sociable animals who play, groom, and communicate with each other. They're known to be found in various places in Asia, Europe, and North America. 🌎

Have you ever encountered these fluffy rodents during your travels? 🦫

📍 Austria

A day's catch via @jacintashackleton. 🐢 Sea turtles absolutely love to munch on jellyfish. Unfortunately, it also means they frequently mistake plastic for their favorite food—so let's keep it out of the ocean! 💙

This was caught on video at the Southern Great Barrier Reef, a mecca for marine life. Here you can find turtles, manta rays, humpback whales, and so much more. It's also known for having one of the most temperate climates on earth, with mild winters and warm summers. ☀️

Have you been to the Southern Great Barrier Reef and did you spot any marine wildlife? 😍

📽 @jacintashackleton

Nature's phenomena via @pepe_soho. 🦋 This was shot in the Monarch Butterfly Biosphere Reserve, a World Heritage Site in Mexico containing most of the overwintering sites of the eastern population of the monarch butterfly. 🇲🇽

"Leaving the sanctuary at the end of the season, I looked up at the sky and I saw thousands and thousands of butterflies leaving the sanctuary towards their places where they came from, either to the USA or Canada."

Every autumn, butterflies from North America return to the site and cluster on the forest reserve. In the spring, they embark on an 8-month migration that takes them all the way to Eastern Canada and back, during which time four consecutive generations are born and die.

How amazing is this? 😍

📸 @pepe_soho 
📍 Monarch Butterfly Biosphere Reserve, Michoacán, Mexico
